==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Torpedo shell
<hw>Torpedo shell</hw>. <fld>(Ordnance)</fld> <def>A shell longer than a
deck-piercing shell, with thinner walls and a larger cavity for the
bursting charge, which consists of about 130 pounds of high explosive.
It has no soft cap, and is intended to effect its damage by the powerful
explosion which follows on slight resistance. It is used chiefly in
12-inch mortars.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Torpedo station</ent>⟦br⟧
